ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A survey of consumer and material culture readings, with a focus on those publications particularly relevant to musicology.
It was a class that provided good exposure to a number of readings, but the order/purpose with which they were assigned was not always clear.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I now have an understanding of the discourse which surrounds musical material culture, and of ways in which this discourse is relevant to any project which I will undertake in the future. Moreover, my final project led me to discover and analyze a source which will likely be useful for many years to come.
The bibliography for the class was unique and widespread, which has given me a good source list for research in the future.
